chunks.html_content: You must tell DVLA if you experience dizziness that is sudden, disabling or recurrent.
chunks.plain_content:
Dizziness or vertigo and driving
You must tell DVLA if you experience dizziness that is sudden, disabling or recurrent.

chunks.html_content: You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.
chunks.plain_content:

chunks.html_content: Fill in form DIZ1 and send it to DVLA. The address is on the form.
